answers.body_markdown:
The Eclipse compiler should show a compiler error like `javac` does. See [Eclipse bug 539105][1].

`javac` behavior is correct and is aligned with the [JLS][2]:

&gt; And if a generic class `C&lt;T&gt;` has a non-generic member class `D`, then the
&gt; member type `C&lt;String&gt;.D` is a parameterized type, even though the class
&gt; `D` is not generic.

Thus, even though the inner class `C` is not generic, the:

    A&lt;? extends B&gt;.C

is a [parameterized type][3], where the type parameter of `A` is an **unknown** subtype of `B`. So, all rules on Generics apply to `C` as well in this context.

Thus, to eliminate compiler error, the type of `y` can be declared as follows:

    List&lt;? extends A&lt;? extends B&gt;.C&gt; y = x.list;

But keep in mind that this won&#39;t allow you to add items to the list `y` (see [PECS][4]).

If it sounds complicated, try to think about it in scope of a simplified example:

    List&lt;Integer&gt; l1 = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    List&lt;Number &gt; l2 = l1; // Error: incompatible types...

    List&lt;? extends Number&gt; l3 = l1; // OK

&lt;hr&gt;

**Additional details:**

The example in the question can be minimized to:

	class A&lt;T&gt; {
	    class C {}
	    List&lt;C&gt; l1 = null;
	    List&lt;A&lt;?&gt;.C&gt; l2 = l1; // Error: incompatible types...
        List&lt;? extends A&lt;?&gt;.C&gt; l3 = l1; // OK
	}

`List&lt;A&lt;?&gt;.C&gt;` is a list of `C` of `A` of unknown type; `C` of arbitrary `A` can be added:

	class A&lt;T&gt; {
	    class C {}
	    C c = new C();
	    void foo(List&lt;A&lt;?&gt;.C&gt; list) {
	        list.add(new A&lt;String&gt;().c);
	        list.add(new A&lt;Number&gt;().c);
	    }
	}

See also:

 - [Is List&amp;lt;Dog&gt; a subclass of List&amp;lt;Animal&gt;? Why are Java generics not implicitly polymorphic?][5]

  [1]: https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=539105
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se13/html/jls-4.html#jls-4.5
  [3]: http://www.angelikalanger.com/GenericsFAQ/FAQSections/ParameterizedTypes.html#FAQ001
  [4]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2723397/what-is-pecs-producer-extends-consumer-super
  [5]: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2745265/is-listdog-a-subclass-of-listanimal-why-are-java-generics-not-implicitly-po

